  "prompt": "What do we call Buffalo meat? Is it bacon?",
  "response": "Buffalo meat is typically referred to as **buffalo** or **bison meat**, as it comes from the American bison (commonly called buffalo). It is not called bacon. Bacon specifically refers to cured and smoked pork belly or other cuts from pigs. Buffalo meat is leaner and has a distinct flavor compared to beef, but it is not related to bacon in any way. If you're looking for a similar product made from buffalo, it would simply be buffalo meat or buffalo steaks, burgers, etc., depending on the cut and preparation.",
